values:
Tomorrow is an important runoff election for Georgia's US&nbsp;Senator and State Court of Appeals.
&nbsp;
For those of you who were supporting Chris McFadden with me, he made a decent showing for his very first attempt at running for political office, but did not make the runoff.&nbsp; He is strongly supporting Sara Doyle for the position.&nbsp;&nbsp;Judges are supposed to impartial and are ethically (though not legally)&nbsp;bound to not engage in telling people what kinds of decisions they intend to make from the bench.&nbsp; Sara Doyle's opponent refused to sign an agreement with most of the other candidates to do just that and keep this race non-partisan.&nbsp; Instead, he has been catering to the religious right.
